place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: Best Starbucks in North Carolina, hands down.
Never had any problems at this location. I place my order ahead and it ready when I arrive
Best Starbucks I've ever been too
I love the staff!!! Jessie is my favorite!!! Reggie is a rockstar. 6am is the best time of the day for me.  They are personable and all around GREAT!!!!
Always good, clean and the staff are super sweet!
Staff is super friendly. Made up a request and they accommodated. Ended up with one of the tastiest drinks I've had at Starbucks. Always quick with having uber orders ready too.
They take longer than most places, but overall great
Super friendly staff and great service. Thank you!
This Starbucks location is consistent in their friendly service and accuracy. This is a great location to order ahead. The predicted pick up time is fairly accurate.

My coffee order was alright. Customer service was awful. Was not greeted properly. Workers didn't seem like wanted to be there... makes me not want to be there. Kaleb working was rude and seemed irritated. Never going back.
Starbucky. Tight parking

Coffee and breakfast egg sandwiches are good. I hate the hoops for collecting, using and losing points, and using credit stored in the app. I feel like Starbucks is training me like a monkey to pull a lever to get a treat.

This location specifically rocks. They always have what they serve, including lids, straws, flavors AND they greet, smile and are personable. All while getting your freshly made menu item pronto. Wish they could all be like this one.
Muy malos

Really lovely Starbucks! The morning crew is cheerful and kind. They made me a drink while I waited for a friend who was late, and while I waited I enjoyed watching them interact with their customers. I'm not a Starbucks person, but I'd come back to this one :)
Friendly environment and staff
People and their issues with other people wearing masks!! Why are you concerned??
Good coffee
Expensive coffee  like any other Starbucks, but if you need caffeine, its the best around!

While I can't speak for the experience after 10AM, I love the early morning crew!! They greet everyone with a smile and consistently create my (usually complicated) drinks correctly the first time, each time. This location feels more like home which is part of the experience we pay for when visiting Starbucks.

I visit during the early morning, school traffic rush and they're always busy but I never wait longer than a few minutes (unless the usual crew is out. Best location is my opinion.
Staff is always friendly, and outdoor seating is available. A "go to" spot for me in the morning!
Always extremely friendly service.
Small but great!!!

Absolutly will not go to another Starbucks again!!! Courtney is amazing and literally went above and beyond out of her way to let me know these cups arrived as I've wanted this one for years!!! Thank you for the best customer service and personal care and time you took to let me know!!! You are the reason I will continue to come here!!!
This location has the BEST staff and coffee.
This starbucks has THE BEST staff!!!
It's a Starbucks. I was there for a meeting.
Love this location. The staff are always friendly.
Grabbed a quick coffee on my way into work and had an excellent experience. Reginald was super friendly, asked about my weekend and everything! Super fast and friendly can't ask for anything more!

Great, friendly staff! Sandwiches made perfectly, and caramel macchiato was made well. Also I'm not sure why people are complaining about wearing a mask, if you haven't noticed this is the expectation every where you go, so be prepared before entering a business so they can stay open. It's disrespectful to the employees who work there and the customers around you.

So pleasant and cute!
WAY better than the nasty gross starbucks on Sharon road!
Freindly workers, short wait, clean store
Stop here everyday ...always good sometime prices are diff tho ..which is weird but idk
Out of everything and not thrilled about being demanded to wear a mask for service even with a exemption from the governor. Will not be going back to this or any Starbucks actually. Very disappointed
Great location even though hidden.  Jane is a superstar.
Great product

This place closes at 8:30, but they were throwing out the food and ready to head out by 7:15.  No snacks available.  You might have more people in here in the evening if you made it seem like you wanted people here in the evening.
The staff are  golden
Great service!
Friendly Staff
Had AAT lemonade for the 1st time here it was very refreshing was not a fan of the dirty bathrooms or the paper trail in spells on all the tables
Starbucks is always consistent
It's Starbucks
Best coffee I have every tasted, pricey but worth it. They are always busy. So be prepare  to wait a good 10mins.
I love this place! Definitely my favorite Starbucks to go to! But could have more drink options on the menu.
This is my go-to Strabucks on the way to work. They never disappoint!
Best Starbucks around the south Charlotte area. They care about their customers. Marilyn needs a raise! Also Austin makes the best drinks hands down.
Busy...divided order into separate delivery parts, bags...this caused confusion...coffee and food choices were hot and good

One of the top 5 starbucks in town when it comes to atmosphere. The staff is friendly. More so than most other Starbucks in town. Perhaps this has to do with manager. He's awesome.

I see a post or two where people talk about their wait time. For whatever it's worth I think this needs to be taken with a grain of salt. First of all these folks get orders out quickly. But here's a first-hand experience. A friend and I went to Starbucks and we were waiting in line with 6 people in front of us. One of those people had a pretty big multiple order. The wait was long for sure. When we had our coffee and sat down my friend proceeded to give this Starbucks a one-star rating due to the wait time. Come on folks.

Another thing you see here, and I love seeing it, is it there are several math tutors who uses Starbucks as their home base. I love watching these teenagers absorb information from these experts. It's a fun Starbucks!
Placed an online order. Store employees chose to ignore the online orders and only make in store orders. Placed online order at 1245, received first drink at 105.

Do like friendly service with side of great coffee and treats? If so this is the place to visit!!! Located at the corner of Carmel Rd. and Quail Hollow " Old Town Harris Teeter kind of tucked away in the back corner. Treat yourself and a friend or loved one!
Good atmosphere. I'm met very nice people every time I've been there. Would recommend.

This has been a destination for me and others almost since it's opening, about 20 years ago. Clean, comfortable, and historically well-managed. Service generally accommodates the variable flow of customers, always provided with a friendly face (which is not always the case with the customers they're trying to serve). Product is well-produced, well-prepared, and reasonably prompt for varying levels of traffic. The number of regulars speaks volumes for this location.
Jamal was so friendly and informative!!!! He made me feel like family...customer service like that is a forgotten art...thank you jamal and keep shining!!!
Yum

The patio tables are dirty dirty. However its a nice shady one to go in summer heat .
Upscale in it patronage.
Ultra caramel frappe is what I ordered. Lots of caramel from top to bottom. Beautiful taste and look. Try one today.
Love the mochas!
WiFi is terrible. Coffee too strong. Noisy din in the lobby.  No point in going.
Everything you'd expect from a Starbucks and they are friendly there.
Very Nice Staff!

On call manager was very kind and helpful. The employee young lady had poor people skills, first I had trouble with order, she had no patience, then I was having trouble with card (chip) she made a big deal about card being declined and how she has been doing her job for 8 years and it was declined in front of other customers, any how the card went through i paid for my order, I was very dissapointed , bad customer experience.
Love my Starbucks

Go here quite often on Monday nights and it's always quite.  A handful of tutoring sessions during the school year and that's about it.  The staff are awesome at this location and extremely friendly and accommodating.

The best Starbucks i've ever been too. Small quite and cozy really allowed me to focus on my work. Friendly and fast service. Chic was truly awesome, will be returning to talk to him and enjoy a great beverage.
Drinks are well made and done very efficiently.
Great service.

This place is a regular location for me. Peak time is Saturday mornings. Avoid waiting in Saturday lines almost out the door by ordering online and you'll be set. Most days this place is quick though. It has limited outdoor seating but inside seating is typical for a Starbucks.
Mike is the best!

Ample seating, friendly staff, great environment and clientele.
One time, my sandwich was a little chilly in the center, and they immediately addressed it and made me a new one with no guff.
AARON SAYS 5 .
Not the fastest service but ample seating and friendly staff
Friendly but slow. Couldn't believe the crowd at this location at 1030 on a Saturday.

Ordered a cold press coffee this morning. No line in front of me. I waited over fifteen minutes to get a beverage that is poured from a pitcher while people ordering after me received expresso beverages from the bar. I called corporate to complain.  I certainly  won't go back to this location . Four people "working" behind the bar and no one could pour a cup of coffee.

Often crowded, noisy and cluttered with merchandise. Service is ok but distracted because so many people go there. Overall Starbucks coffee is bitter and overpriced, with snacks that are also overpriced.

Ali Robert's - I come here everyday, and I know the staff is excellent - especially Skylar She is in high school and deserves better than having her name mentioned in a bad light on the public Internet Reviewing the place of business is fine-mentioning a minor's name publicly is in poor taste and frankly rude
The best Starbucks around. They are always fast, accurate, and pleasant.

I came to this location today and the service was terrible. It took about 30 minutes for me to even order. When i came up to the register the cashier, Skylar, cut me off several times and ended up not even getting my order right. She actually ended up messing up several people's orders...  They also ran out of venti cups and mango?? I don't understand how that happens but i was completely unsatisfied with the experience here.
This is not a place to come socialize.  I have been here at various times and no one here or the ones here are not sociable.  Come in for coffee and leave.

I love the cold brew, this Starbucks has some patio seating, although its sort of on the sidewalk of the shopping center so it's not the best for an intimate conversation or a meeting. The parking is a little difficult to get in and out of, so tough spot for a quick grab. Overall not bad, but I usually don't meet people at this location.
Takes for ever for orders, even when two people are in line.
Very friendly staff every time I've been here.
Friends don't let friends drink Starbucks.
This is a tucked away location with adequate seating. Friendly service. Only a few comfy chairs though. I would patronize this location again when in the area.

Surly staff.

As you will see, this location is staffed by mostly cranky old men who could care less about their jobs. I asked for another drink because I didn't like mine and after it came out a barista told me, to my face, "Let me know if you don't like that one too". Really disappointed Starbucks.
Slow and not very good. They miss brew coffee frequently. The evening crew is oblivious to customers.
